    "long_instructions": "### Loops & Cues\r\n\r\nGreat performers know that surprises are part of the magic of live music. Just like a DJ adjusting a mix on the fly or a band improvising during a concert, you'll practice reacting to unexpected changes in your performance using a new `random` block. We'll learn more about this block in the next lesson - for now: follow the steps below!\r\n\r\n**Do This**:\r\n- There are 3 tracks inside the `play random` block - update them to be three different vocal tracks from Fireworks by Katy Perry [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:play_workspace)\r\n- Add your own backing beat and bass track to the vocals [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-lightbulb\"></i> <i class=\"fa-solid fa-square-right\"></i>](#clickable=id:repeat_workspace)\r\n- Create 3 triggers that start on the \"next beat\" - one for each of the vocal tracks. Inside each trigger, add a small loop and a few tracks to play that go with each track\r\n- Perform! As you play, one of the vocal tracks will be randomly chosen to play. React in real-time to each vocal track, adjusting your timing as needed.\r\n\r\n",
